Class Detector

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.uc3m.baldo.opinais.core.detectors.Detector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Detector>

    public class Detector
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Detector>, java.lang.Cloneable
    Detector.

    Represents a detector in the Artificial Immune System, which simulates an antibody in a natural immune system.

    The detector is specialized in detecting either self or nonself individuals, and is represented by an schema.

    Author:
    Alejandro Baldominos

    • Constructor Detail

      • Detector

        public Detector(Type type,
        Bit[] threshold,
        Bit[] pattern,
        Bit[] mask)

        Builds a new Detector instance.

        Parameters:
        type - the detector type (either SELF or NON_SELF).
        threshold - a number in Gray encoding, so that threshold / 255 represents the minimum percentage of bit matches between the schema and the individual to consider a match.
        pattern - an array of bits representing the pattern.
        mask - an array of bits, containing a 1 in those positions which are considered as wildcards.

    • Method Detail

      • match

        public double match(Individual individual)

        Checks whether the detector actually detects the individual.

        This will happen when the percentage of bit matches (ignoring wildcards) exceeds the threshold.

        Parameters:
        individual - the individual which is tried to be matched.
        Returns:
        true if the detector matches the individual, false otherwise.
